    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-08-26T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-08-26T08:00:00-05:00" n="533"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d533">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/8–2654: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the united Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Butterworth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-08-26T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 26, 1954—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>989. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 1006, August 19.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d533fn1">See footnote 1, <ref target="#pg_754">p. 754</ref>.</note>
                    In course informal conversation Foreign Office, Embassy officer received
                    distinct impression <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> will not go beyond terms
                    last year’s moratorium agreement re Chinese representation problem in <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>, and will insist on specific time limit. Embassy
                    understands ministerial decision expected momentarily and will be transmitted
                    through British Embassy Washington.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Butterworth</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
